    • start

      public void start()
      Description copied from class: AbstractComponentRegistry
      This starts the components in the registry, connecting to channels, starting service threads, etc. If the component is not in the ComponentStatus.INITIALIZING state, it will be initialized first.

      You need to call AbstractComponentRegistry.postStart() after this completes with no error to complete startup. This is necessary as some post start steps can fail and this allows the user to handle that case before stopping the registry.

      Specified by:
      start in interface Lifecycle
      Overrides:
      start in class AbstractComponentRegistry

    • delayStart

      protected CompletionStage<Void> delayStart()
      The ComponentRegistry may delay the start after a cluster shutdown. The component waits for the installation of the previous stable topology to start. Caches that do not need state transfer or are private do not need to delay the start.
      Specified by:
      delayStart in class AbstractComponentRegistry

    • rewire

      public void rewire()
      Description copied from class: AbstractComponentRegistry
      Rewires components. Used to rewire components in the CR if a cache has been stopped (moved to state TERMINATED), which would (almost) empty the registry of components. Rewiring will re-inject all dependencies so that the cache can be started again.
      Overrides:
      rewire in class AbstractComponentRegistry
